  "name": "haunted-manor",
  "description": "Old, historic, haunted-house mood \u2014 warm-brown darkness with candlelight amber and a ghostly cold-teal accent. Color theory: near-analogous warm-brown base (hue ~30 deg) with an amber primary accent for warmth/light sources, and a desaturated cold teal secondary accent for a near-complementary supernatural pop. Verified WCAG AA+ contrast for body text; warn/danger separated by luminance (not hue alone) for color-blind accessibility. Two custom faces, per the 2-font rule: URW Algerian for panel titles/headings (an ornate display face already used for Houdini's PxC clock numerals, restored here for titles), AlmendraSC for body text/labels/buttons (an elegant gothic small-caps face, Houdini's original body font).",
